center.font: Visit the new Geocaching Ireland discussion forum HERE

long-description.p: A small park located in the centre of Sandymount village with a bust commemorating the poet W.B. Yeats, who was born in Sandymount.
The National Library is holding an exhibition based on W.B. Yeats from early June 2006, if you are interested in finding out more about the poet's life and interests.
You will need to bring a pencil or pen with you to sign the log!

element.encoded-hints: In the same place as that cheque I promised you!
